{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Hwd8EdPbCobp7hNAxqWsnt","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Complete Contents of All Java Source Files\n\nI've read all 47 Java source files from the DayTrader application. Below are the complete contents of each file:\n\n### 1. MarketSummaryDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/MarketSummaryDataBean.java`\n\nA data bean representing market summary with TSIA (Trade Stock Index Average), volume, top gainers and losers. Contains methods to generate random instances and display market data. Removed javax.json dependency in favor of Jackson.\n\n### 2. RunStatsDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/RunStatsDataBean.java`\n\nSerializable bean storing runtime statistics including trade user count, stock count, login/logout counts, holdings, and orders. Used for database reset operations.\n\n### 3. RuntimeMode.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/RuntimeMode.java`\n\nCDI qualifier annotation for selecting runtime mode (defaults to \"Full EJB3\"). Uses jakarta.inject.Qualifier for dependency injection.\n\n### 4. QuotePriceChange.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/QuotePriceChange.java`\n\nCDI qualifier annotation for quote price change events.\n\n### 5. MarketSummaryUpdate.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/MarketSummaryUpdate.java`\n\nCDI qualifier annotation for market summary update events.\n\n### 6. TradeServices.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeServices.java`\n\nMain interface defining all trade business operations including buy/sell stock, manage orders, quotes, accounts, and user authentication. Core of the trading application.\n\n### 7. TradeSession2Direct.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeSession2Direct.java`\n\nCDI qualifier for \"Session to Direct\" runtime mode.\n\n### 8. TradeJDBC.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeJDBC.java`\n\nCDI qualifier for Direct JDBC runtime mode.\n\n### 9. TradeEJB.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeEJB.java`\n\nCDI qualifier for EJB3 runtime mode.\n\n### 10. Trace.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/Trace.java`\n\nInterceptor binding annotation for tracing method calls. Uses @InterceptorBinding and @Inherited.\n\n### 11. TradeDB.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeDB.java`\n\nInterface for database operations including resetTrade() and checkDBProductName().\n\n### 12. QuoteDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/QuoteDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity representing stock quotes with symbol, company, price, volume. Includes named queries for retrieving quotes. Migrated to jakarta.persistence.\n\n### 13. AccountProfileDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountProfileDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity for user account profiles with userID, password, fullname, address, email, credit card. One-to-one relationship with AccountDataBean.\n\n### 14. OrderDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/OrderDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity for buy/sell orders with order type, status, dates, quantity, price, fees. Relationships to Account, Quote, and Holding entities. Uses IDENTITY strategy for ID generation.\n\n### 15. HoldingDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/HoldingDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity representing stock holdings with quantity, purchase price/date. Many-to-one relationships with Account and Quote entities.\n\n### 16. AccountDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity for user accounts with balance, login counts, creation date. One-to-one with AccountProfile, one-to-many with Orders and Holdings. Includes login/logout business logic.\n\n### 17. DirectSLSBBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/session2direct/DirectSLSBBean.java`\n\nSession bean for \"Session to Direct\" mode. Delegates to TradeDirect (JDBC) implementation. Migrated from @Stateless to @ApplicationScoped with @Transactional.\n\n### 18. TradeSLSBBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/TradeSLSBBean.java`\n\nDefault TradeServices implementation using JPA and EntityManager. Migrated from @Stateless EJB to @ApplicationScoped CDI bean. Includes buy/sell/order management, quote operations, and user account management. Uses MessageProducerService for messaging.\n\n### 19. MarketSummarySingleton.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/MarketSummarySingleton.java`\n\nApplicationScoped bean computing market summary (TSIA, volume, top gainers/losers). Updates every 20 seconds using @Scheduled. Migrated from @Singleton EJB with @Lock to synchronized methods.\n\n### 20. AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java`\n\nRequestScoped bean for submitting orders asynchronously with 500ms delay. Uses Quarkus VirtualThreads ExecutorService instead of ManagedScheduledExecutorService.\n\n### 21. AsyncScheduledOrder.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrder.java`\n\nDependent scoped Runnable for completing orders asynchronously. Selects appropriate TradeServices implementation based on runtime mode.\n\n### 22. TradeDirectDBUtils.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirectDBUtils.java`\n\nApplicationScoped bean for database operations including buildDB, recreateDBTables, resetTrade. Uses AgroalDataSource (Quarkus data source).\n\n### 23. TradeDirect.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirect.java`\n\nDirect JDBC implementation of TradeServices (1807 lines). Uses raw SQL for all operations. Qualified with @TradeJDBC. Handles transactions via UserTransaction. Replaces JMS with MessageProducerService.\n\n### 24. AsyncOrder.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrder.java`\n\nDependent scoped Runnable for asynchronously completing orders via JDBC. Uses @Transactional annotation.\n\n### 25. KeySequenceDirect.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/KeySequenceDirect.java`\n\nUtility for generating unique IDs from database key table. Allocates blocks of IDs for performance.\n\n### 26. AsyncOrderSubmitter.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrderSubmitter.java`\n\nRequestScoped bean submitting async orders using VirtualThreads ExecutorService.\n\n### 27. QuoteUpdateMessage.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/QuoteUpdateMessage.java`\n\nPOJO representing quote update messages. Replaces JMS TextMessage with simple Java object. Contains symbol, price, oldPrice, company details, etc.\n\n### 28. OrderMessage.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/OrderMessage.java`\n\nPOJO for order messages (neworder, ping commands). Replaces JMS message properties with simple fields.\n\n### 29. MessageProducerService.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessageProducerService.java`\n\nApplicationScoped service using SmallRye Reactive Messaging (@Channel + Emitter). Replaces JMS ConnectionFactory/Producer pattern. Sends to trade-broker-queue and trade-streamer-topic.\n\n### 30. TradeResource.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/TradeResource.java`\n\nJAX-RS REST endpoints at /trade for market summary, login/logout, account operations, buy/sell orders, registration.\n\n### 31. QuoteResource.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/QuoteResource.java`\n\nJAX-RS resource at /quotes for retrieving stock quotes by symbols.\n\n### 32. MessagingResource.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/MessagingResource.java`\n\nREST endpoints at /messaging for testing ping messages to broker/streamer, and viewing MDB statistics. Replaces PingServlet2MDBQueue/Topic servlets.\n\n### 33. DTStreamer3MDB.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTStreamer3MDB.java`\n\nApplicationScoped message listener for trade-streamer-topic using @Incoming. Processes quote updates and ping messages. Replaces @MessageDriven EJB.\n\n### 34. DTBroker3MDB.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTBroker3MDB.java`\n\nApplicationScoped @Transactional listener for trade-broker-queue. Processes neworder and ping messages. Completes orders asynchronously.\n\n### 35. TradeAppResource.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/TradeAppResource.java`\n\nJAX-RS web interface at /app replacing TradeAppServlet. Provides HTML responses for login, portfolio, account, quotes, buy/sell operations. Simple HTML instead of JSP.\n\n### 36. TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java`\n\nAnnotationLiteral implementation for RuntimeMode qualifier. Used for CDI bean selection.\n\n### 37. TradeConfig.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeConfig.java`\n\nConfiguration class (425 lines) with runtime modes, database scaling parameters, scenario mixes, random data generation utilities, order fees, penny stock handling.\n\n### 38. TimerStat.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TimerStat.java`\n\nSimple statistics tracker for min/max/average timing data.\n\n### 39. RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java`\n\nApplicationScoped bean maintaining last 5 stock changes. Fires CDI events on price changes. Uses CopyOnWriteArrayList.\n\n### 40. KeyBlock.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/KeyBlock.java`\n\nAbstractSequentialList for managing ranges of primary key IDs.\n\n### 41. Log.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/Log.java`\n\nLogging utility using java.util.logging.Logger. Provides info, error, trace, debug methods.\n\n### 42. FinancialUtils.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/FinancialUtils.java`\n\nFinancial calculations for gains, percentages, holdings totals. Uses RoundingMode.HALF_UP for BigDecimal operations.\n\n### 43. MDBStats.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/MDBStats.java`\n\nSingleton HashMap tracking message processing statistics. Thread-safe timing collection.\n\n### 44. DatabasePopulator.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/startup/DatabasePopulator.java`\n\nApplicationScoped bean populating database on startup with quotes and users. Observes StartupEvent. Configurable via application.properties.\n\n### 45. TradeResourceTest.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/TradeResourceTest.java`\n\nQuarkusTest for /rest/trade/market endpoint.\n\n### 46. MessagingTest.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingTest.java`\n\nTests for JMS to Reactive Messaging migration. Verifies broker ping, streamer ping, quote updates, and async order processing.\n\n### 47. MessagingResourceTest.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingResourceTest.java`\n\nREST API tests for messaging endpoints: ping broker/streamer, get/reset stats.\n\n---\n\nThis DayTrader application is a complete Jakarta EE to Quarkus migration featuring:\n- **Persistence:** JPA entities with jakarta.persistence\n- **CDI:** @ApplicationScoped, @RequestScoped, @Inject\n- **Transactions:** @Transactional\n- **Messaging:** SmallRye Reactive Messaging (@Incoming, @Channel, Emitter)\n- **REST:** JAX-RS resources\n- **Scheduling:** @Scheduled for periodic tasks\n- **Virtual Threads:** Quarkus VirtualThreads ExecutorService\n\nAll code uses modern Jakarta EE 9+ APIs and Quarkus-specific features."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"ff331e6a-b106-4e3f-b223-78f933134030"}
