{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01H3MdPqtWhm4ERXJbt7zv8X","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_014qamibEibMumQgzLy1EDzY","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Write application.properties and main class","prompt":"I need you to write TWO files for a Quarkus to Spring Boot migration:\n\n1. Write `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/application.properties` with this content:\n\n```\n# Spring Boot Application Configuration\nspring.application.name=daytrader\n\n# HTTP port\nserver.port=8080\nserver.servlet.context-path=/\n\n# ===========================================\n# Database Configuration\n# ===========================================\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\nspring.datasource.username=sa\nspring.datasource.password=\nspring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.h2.Driver\n\n# JPA/Hibernate\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n\n# ===========================================\n# REST Configuration  \n# ===========================================\n# Spring MVC base path for REST controllers\nspring.mvc.servlet.path=/rest\n\n# ===========================================\n# Trade Application Configuration\n# ===========================================\ntrade.runtime-mode=EJB3\ntrade.order-processing-mode=SYNCH\ntrade.max-users=50\ntrade.max-quotes=100\n\n# Database population on startup\ntrade.db.populate.on.startup=true\n\n# ===========================================\n# Actuator (Health checks)\n# ===========================================\nmanagement.endpoints.web.exposure.include=health,info\nmanagement.endpoint.health.show-details=always\n\n# ===========================================\n# Jackson Configuration\n# ===========================================\nspring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\nspring.jackson.serialization.write-dates-as-timestamps=true\n```\n\n2. Write `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java` with this content:\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableAsync;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@EnableScheduling\n@EnableAsync\npublic class DayTraderApplication {\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(DayTraderApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nRead the files first if they already exist, then overwrite them.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2477,"cache_read_input_tokens":123805,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2477,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1979},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"0a37caa2-ae10-409e-a3e4-1b92478ab905"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01H3MdPqtWhm4ERXJbt7zv8X","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01S3bMaPQhx8E18Du7cTWPBt","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Rewrite entity classes for Spring","prompt":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need you to read and then rewrite all entity classes and bean classes. The entities use standard JPA annotations (jakarta.persistence) which are fine for Spring Boot. The main changes needed are:\n- Remove any CDI annotations and replace with Spring equivalents where needed\n- Entities mostly just need their imports cleaned up (they should already use jakarta.persistence)\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\nFiles to check and update as needed:\n1. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/QuoteDataBean.java\n2. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountProfileDataBean.java\n3. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/OrderDataBean.java\n4. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/HoldingDataBean.java\n5. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountDataBean.java\n6. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/MarketSummaryDataBean.java\n7. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/RunStatsDataBean.java\n\nRead each file first, then if it has any Quarkus-specific imports or annotations, rewrite it. If it only uses standard JPA/Jakarta imports, leave it as-is.\n\nThe entities should use standard Jakarta Persistence annotations which work fine with Spring Boot 3.x since Spring Boot 3.x uses Jakarta namespace.\n\nReport back what files needed changes and what files were left as-is.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2477,"cache_read_input_tokens":123805,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2477,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1979},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"8b4378d9-d164-4dcf-bd92-b696bc2dbbcb"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01H3MdPqtWhm4ERXJbt7zv8X","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_017ixXZeH5VsrCPU3VwJakeq","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Rewrite Dockerfile for Spring Boot","prompt":"Read and rewrite the Dockerfile at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/Dockerfile\n\nReplace the Quarkus-based Dockerfile with a Spring Boot one. The new Dockerfile should:\n1. Use maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble as the base image (same as before)\n2. Install Python, Playwright (same as before for smoke tests)\n3. Build with `mvn clean package -DskipTests`\n4. Run with `java -jar target/daytrader-spring-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar`\n\nWrite this exact content:\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n\nUSER root\n# install uv\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full \\\n    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n\nENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\nENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\nRUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n\n# create venv and install\nRUN uv venv /opt/venv \\\n    && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n\nENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\nRUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n\n# Set working directory\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy all the assets\nCOPY . .\n\nRUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n\n# Build the application at image build time\nRUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n\nCMD [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"target/daytrader-spring-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\"]\n```","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2477,"cache_read_input_tokens":123805,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2477,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1979},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"3c339943-e7ae-45a9-bef8-2f1e7165265c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need you to write TWO files for a Quarkus to Spring Boot migration:\n\n1. Write `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/application.properties` with this content:\n\n```\n# Spring Boot Application Configuration\nspring.application.name=daytrader\n\n# HTTP port\nserver.port=8080\nserver.servlet.context-path=/\n\n# ===========================================\n# Database Configuration\n# ===========================================\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\nspring.datasource.username=sa\nspring.datasource.password=\nspring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.h2.Driver\n\n# JPA/Hibernate\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n\n# ===========================================\n# REST Configuration  \n# ===========================================\n# Spring MVC base path for REST controllers\nspring.mvc.servlet.path=/rest\n\n# ===========================================\n# Trade Application Configuration\n# ===========================================\ntrade.runtime-mode=EJB3\ntrade.order-processing-mode=SYNCH\ntrade.max-users=50\ntrade.max-quotes=100\n\n# Database population on startup\ntrade.db.populate.on.startup=true\n\n# ===========================================\n# Actuator (Health checks)\n# ===========================================\nmanagement.endpoints.web.exposure.include=health,info\nmanagement.endpoint.health.show-details=always\n\n# ===========================================\n# Jackson Configuration\n# ===========================================\nspring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\nspring.jackson.serialization.write-dates-as-timestamps=true\n```\n\n2. Write `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java` with this content:\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableAsync;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@EnableScheduling\n@EnableAsync\npublic class DayTraderApplication {\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(DayTraderApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nRead the files first if they already exist, then overwrite them."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014qamibEibMumQgzLy1EDzY","session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"4b554ce3-a960-4297-8718-c5a9bce4e1ae"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need you to read and then rewrite all entity classes and bean classes. The entities use standard JPA annotations (jakarta.persistence) which are fine for Spring Boot. The main changes needed are:\n- Remove any CDI annotations and replace with Spring equivalents where needed\n- Entities mostly just need their imports cleaned up (they should already use jakarta.persistence)\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\nFiles to check and update as needed:\n1. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/QuoteDataBean.java\n2. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountProfileDataBean.java\n3. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/OrderDataBean.java\n4. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/HoldingDataBean.java\n5. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountDataBean.java\n6. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/MarketSummaryDataBean.java\n7. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/RunStatsDataBean.java\n\nRead each file first, then if it has any Quarkus-specific imports or annotations, rewrite it. If it only uses standard JPA/Jakarta imports, leave it as-is.\n\nThe entities should use standard Jakarta Persistence annotations which work fine with Spring Boot 3.x since Spring Boot 3.x uses Jakarta namespace.\n\nReport back what files needed changes and what files were left as-is."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01S3bMaPQhx8E18Du7cTWPBt","session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"92ef1db0-b99c-4846-8c51-e8fcc472e454"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Read and rewrite the Dockerfile at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/Dockerfile\n\nReplace the Quarkus-based Dockerfile with a Spring Boot one. The new Dockerfile should:\n1. Use maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble as the base image (same as before)\n2. Install Python, Playwright (same as before for smoke tests)\n3. Build with `mvn clean package -DskipTests`\n4. Run with `java -jar target/daytrader-spring-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar`\n\nWrite this exact content:\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n\nUSER root\n# install uv\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full \\\n    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n\nENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\nENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\nRUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n\n# create venv and install\nRUN uv venv /opt/venv \\\n    && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n\nENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\nRUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n\n# Set working directory\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy all the assets\nCOPY . .\n\nRUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n\n# Build the application at image build time\nRUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n\nCMD [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"target/daytrader-spring-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\"]\n```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017ixXZeH5VsrCPU3VwJakeq","session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"7bc6988b-be12-4a93-becc-d963dfeba450"}
