{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RZFNPkZndh9VFXfzW48vCc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Quarkus Application Configuration\n     2→# This replaces web.xml, persistence.xml, and server.xml configurations\n     3→\n     4→# Application name\n     5→quarkus.application.name=daytrader\n     6→\n     7→# HTTP port (similar to testServerHttpPort in original)\n     8→quarkus.http.port=8080\n     9→\n    10→# ===========================================\n    11→# Database Configuration (replaces persistence.xml)\n    12→# ===========================================\n    13→# Using H2 in-memory database (similar to Derby in original)\n    14→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\n    15→quarkus.datasource.username=sa\n    16→quarkus.datasource.password=\n    17→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\n    18→\n    19→# Hibernate ORM configuration\n    20→quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n    21→quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n    22→quarkus.hibernate-orm.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\n    23→\n    24→# ===========================================\n    25→# REST Configuration\n    26→# ===========================================\n    27→# Base path for REST APIs (replaces @ApplicationPath(\"/rest\"))\n    28→quarkus.rest.path=/rest\n    29→\n    30→# ===========================================\n    31→# Trade Application Configuration\n    32→# ===========================================\n    33→# These replace TradeConfig static values - now externalized\n    34→trade.runtime-mode=EJB3\n    35→trade.order-processing-mode=SYNCH\n    36→trade.max-users=50\n    37→trade.max-quotes=100\n    38→\n    39→# Database population on startup (set to false to disable auto-population)\n    40→trade.db.populate.on.startup=true\n    41→\n    42→# ===========================================\n    43→# Development Mode\n    44→# ===========================================\n    45→%dev.quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=true\n    46→%dev.quarkus.log.level=INFO\n    47→%dev.quarkus.log.category.\"com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader\".level=DEBUG\n    48→\n    49→# ===========================================\n    50→# Reactive Messaging Configuration (replaces JMS)\n    51→# ===========================================\n    52→# MIGRATION NOTES:\n    53→# Original Jakarta EE JMS resources:\n    54→#   jms/QueueConnectionFactory -> ConnectionFactory for queues\n    55→#   jms/TopicConnectionFactory -> ConnectionFactory for topics  \n    56→#   jms/TradeBrokerQueue -> Queue for order processing (DTBroker3MDB)\n    57→#   jms/TradeStreamerTopic -> Topic for quote updates (DTStreamer3MDB)\n    58→#\n    59→# Quarkus SmallRye Reactive Messaging:\n    60→#   - Uses channels instead of JMS destinations\n    61→#   - In-memory connector for dev/test (can switch to Kafka/AMQP in prod)\n    62→#   - merge=true allows multiple consumers on same channel\n    63→\n    64→# Trade Broker Queue (for order processing)\n    65→# No external connector - use internal in-memory channels\n    66→# The @Broadcast annotation on emitter connects to @Incoming consumers\n    67→\n    68→# Trade Streamer Topic (for quote updates)\n    69→# No external connector - use internal in-memory channels\n    70→\n    71→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014qamibEibMumQgzLy1EDzY","session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"0aed3c9e-21bb-409e-9adf-8be7367a8d46"}
