{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01BUPSw2daEAzTLjakJtxx5Z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me rewrite all the Quarkus-specific Java files. I'll use multiple parallel agents for efficiency:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":602,"cache_read_input_tokens":130573,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":602,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":10017},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"f38e4bb7-ddea-4e89-9b8f-d400545bc780"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01BUPSw2daEAzTLjakJtxx5Z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012M7gsRgZQL4Pbtw8LRDtTj","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Rewrite REST controllers for Spring","prompt":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need to rewrite 4 REST resource files from JAX-RS (Quarkus) to Spring MVC (Spring Boot).\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\nIMPORTANT: The application.properties sets `spring.mvc.servlet.path=/rest` which means all Spring MVC endpoints are automatically prefixed with `/rest`. So paths in the controllers should NOT include `/rest`.\n\nIMPORTANT: In the original Quarkus app, `TradeServices` was injected via CDI `@Inject`. In Spring, this becomes `@Autowired` or constructor injection. Since `TradeServices` is an interface with multiple implementations, we need to use `@Qualifier` or `@Primary`. The `TradeSLSBBean` is the default (was `@Default` in CDI).\n\n### File 1: TradeResource.java\nRead `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/TradeResource.java` and rewrite it:\n\nReplace:\n- `jakarta.ws.rs.*` imports → `org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped` → `@RestController`\n- `jakarta.inject.Inject` → `@Autowired`\n- `@Path(\"trade\")` → `@RequestMapping(\"/trade\")`\n- `@GET @Path(\"/market\")` → `@GetMapping(\"/market\")`\n- `@POST @Path(\"/login\")` → `@PostMapping(\"/login\")`\n- `@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)` → nothing (use @RequestParam)\n- `@FormParam(\"x\")` → `@RequestParam(\"x\")`\n- `@PathParam(\"x\")` → `@PathVariable(\"x\")`\n- `@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)` → (handled by @RestController)\n- `Response.ok(x).build()` → `ResponseEntity.ok(x)`\n- `Response.serverError().entity(x).build()` → `ResponseEntity.status(500).body(x)`\n- `Response.status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED)` → `ResponseEntity.status(401)`\n- `Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build()` → `ResponseEntity.notFound().build()`\n- `Response` return type → `ResponseEntity<?>`\n\n### File 2: QuoteResource.java\nRead and rewrite similarly:\n- Same JAX-RS → Spring MVC conversion\n- `@Path(\"quotes\")` → `@RequestMapping(\"/quotes\")`\n\n### File 3: MessagingResource.java\nRead and rewrite similarly:\n- `@Path(\"/messaging\")` → `@RequestMapping(\"/messaging\")`\n- `@QueryParam` → `@RequestParam`\n\n### File 4: TradeAppResource.java (at web/TradeAppResource.java)\nRead and rewrite similarly:\n- `@Path(\"/app\")` → `@RequestMapping(\"/app\")`\n- `@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)` → methods return `ResponseEntity<String>` with `produces = \"text/html\"`\n- Update form action URLs from `/rest/app` to `/rest/app` (keep as-is since spring.mvc.servlet.path=/rest handles it)\n\nFor ALL files, use `@Autowired` for TradeServices injection. Since we'll mark TradeSLSBBean as `@Primary`, no qualifier is needed.\n\nRead each file first, then write the updated version.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":602,"cache_read_input_tokens":130573,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":602,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":10017},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"c2942a0b-6af0-4959-8689-59bda2f44f14"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01BUPSw2daEAzTLjakJtxx5Z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Uc6kGPVjfMPcWC9DhiMNbo","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Rewrite service impl classes for Spring","prompt":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need to rewrite all service implementation classes.\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\nMigration rules:\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` → `@org.springframework.stereotype.Service`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped` → `@org.springframework.stereotype.Service` with `@org.springframework.context.annotation.Scope(\"prototype\")`  \n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent` → `@org.springframework.stereotype.Component` with `@org.springframework.context.annotation.Scope(\"prototype\")`\n- `jakarta.inject.Inject` → `@org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired`\n- `jakarta.transaction.Transactional` → `@org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional`\n- `jakarta.persistence.EntityManager` with `@Inject` → `@PersistenceContext EntityManager`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.event.Event` → Remove (replace with Spring's ApplicationEventPublisher or simply remove unused events)\n- `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Default` → Remove\n- `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any` / `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance` → Remove/simplify\n- CDI qualifier annotations like `@TradeEJB`, `@TradeJDBC`, `@TradeSession2Direct` → Use Spring `@Qualifier`\n- `@RuntimeMode(\"...\")` → Remove (custom CDI qualifier)\n- `@Trace` → Remove (custom CDI interceptor binding)\n- `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled` → `@org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Scheduled`\n- `io.quarkus.virtual.threads.VirtualThreads` → Use standard Java `Executors.newVirtualThreadPerTaskExecutor()` or `Executors.newCachedThreadPool()`\n- `io.quarkus.narayana.jta.QuarkusTransaction` → Remove (not used directly)\n- `io.agroal.api.AgroalDataSource` → `javax.sql.DataSource`\n- `org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty` → `@org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value`\n- `io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent` → Use `@PostConstruct` or `ApplicationReadyEvent`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes` → Remove (use Spring event or @PostConstruct)\n- `@jakarta.annotation.Resource` → `@Autowired`\n- `jakarta.transaction.UserTransaction` → Remove (use Spring's `@Transactional` or `PlatformTransactionManager`)\n- CDI `Event<String>` for firing async events → Remove or replace with `ApplicationEventPublisher`\n- `@io.smallrye.reactive.messaging.annotations.Broadcast` → Remove\n- `org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel` → Remove  \n- `org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter` → Remove\n- `org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming` → Remove\n- `@jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull` / `@NotEmpty` → Keep (works with Spring validation)\n- `jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct` → Keep (works in Spring)\n\n### Files to rewrite:\n\n**1. TradeSLSBBean.java** (impl/ejb3/) - This is the PRIMARY TradeServices implementation. Mark it with `@Service` and `@Primary`. Replace `@Inject EntityManager` with `@PersistenceContext EntityManager`. Replace `@Inject MessageProducerService` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject MarketSummarySingleton` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject RecentQuotePriceChangeList` with `@Autowired`. Remove `@Default`, `@TradeEJB`, `@RuntimeMode`, `@Trace`. Keep `@Transactional` but change to Spring's. Keep all business logic exactly the same.\n\n**2. MarketSummarySingleton.java** (impl/ejb3/) - Replace `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Service`. Replace `@Inject EntityManager` with `@PersistenceContext`. Replace `@Inject @MarketSummaryUpdate Event<String>` with removal (or `@Autowired ApplicationEventPublisher`). Replace `@Scheduled(every = \"20s\")` with `@Scheduled(fixedRate = 20000)`. The method `updateMarketSummary()` needs `@Transactional` since it accesses the EntityManager.\n\n**3. AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java** (impl/ejb3/) - Replace `@RequestScoped` with `@Component @Scope(\"prototype\")`. Remove `@Inject @VirtualThreads ExecutorService` - instead create a regular ExecutorService field. Replace `@Inject AsyncScheduledOrder` with `@Autowired ApplicationContext` and get bean from context (since it's prototype-scoped).\n\n**4. AsyncScheduledOrder.java** (impl/ejb3/) - Replace `@Dependent` with `@Component @Scope(\"prototype\")`. The constructor currently uses CDI `Instance<TradeServices>` with qualifiers. In Spring, just inject the primary `TradeServices` with `@Autowired`.\n\n**5. TradeDirect.java** (impl/direct/) - Replace `@Dependent` with `@Component(\"tradeDirect\") @Scope(\"prototype\")`. Replace `@Inject DataSource` with `@Autowired DataSource`. Replace `@Inject UserTransaction` → Remove UserTransaction, manage transactions manually via DataSource connections (already does manual commits). Replace `@Inject RecentQuotePriceChangeList` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject AsyncOrderSubmitter` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject @MarketSummaryUpdate Event<String>` with nothing (remove). Replace `@Inject MessageProducerService` with `@Autowired`. Remove `@TradeJDBC`, `@RuntimeMode`, `@Trace` qualifiers. Remove `io.quarkus.narayana.jta.QuarkusTransaction` import.\n\n**6. TradeDirectDBUtils.java** (impl/direct/) - Replace `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Service`. Replace `@Inject AgroalDataSource` with `@Autowired DataSource`. Replace `@Inject @TradeJDBC TradeServices` with `@Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\") TradeServices`.\n\n**7. AsyncOrder.java** (impl/direct/) - Replace `@Dependent` with `@Component @Scope(\"prototype\")`. Replace `@Inject @TradeJDBC TradeServices` with `@Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\") TradeServices`. Keep `@Transactional` but use Spring's.\n\n**8. AsyncOrderSubmitter.java** (impl/direct/) - Replace `@RequestScoped` with `@Component @Scope(\"prototype\")`. Remove `@VirtualThreads`. Use `Executors.newCachedThreadPool()`.\n\n**9. DirectSLSBBean.java** (impl/session2direct/) - Replace `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Service(\"directSLSBBean\")`. Replace `@Inject @TradeJDBC TradeServices` with `@Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\") TradeServices`. Replace `@Inject AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter` with `@Autowired`. Remove `@TradeSession2Direct`, `@RuntimeMode`, `@Trace`. Keep `@Transactional` but Spring's.\n\nRead each file, rewrite it with the above transformations. Preserve ALL business logic exactly. Just change annotations and imports.\n\nCRITICAL: For TradeDirect.java, the `UserTransaction txn` field that was injected is used for global transactions. Since Spring doesn't have UserTransaction in the same way, replace the `txn` field with `@Autowired PlatformTransactionManager transactionManager` and use `TransactionStatus` / `TransactionTemplate` OR simply remove the UserTransaction usage since the direct JDBC mode already manages its own commits/rollbacks via Connection. The easiest approach: replace `txn.begin()`, `txn.commit()`, `txn.rollback()` with NO-OP or with connection-level transaction management that's already in place. Actually, the safest is to just use `@Autowired org.springframework.transaction.PlatformTransactionManager txnManager` and then `TransactionDefinition def = new DefaultTransactionDefinition(); TransactionStatus status = txnManager.getTransaction(def);` etc. But that's complex. The simplest: just keep the field but autowire a `javax.transaction.UserTransaction` - but Spring doesn't provide one directly.\n\nSIMPLEST APPROACH for TradeDirect: Remove UserTransaction entirely. The code already has manual connection commit/rollback. For the `ASYNCH_2PHASE` mode paths that use `txn.begin()/commit()/rollback()`, simply make the transaction boundary be managed by the connection itself (the connection is already not auto-commit). Set `inGlobalTxn=false` always in those paths so the existing connection-level commit/rollback handles it.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":602,"cache_read_input_tokens":130573,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":602,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":10017},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"8b711ac7-797c-40da-b2bf-9bf43533c44e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01BUPSw2daEAzTLjakJtxx5Z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01UsBY2Qg5wdBJM2V5RHeTYS","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Rewrite messaging and MDB classes for Spring","prompt":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need to rewrite the messaging classes.\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\nThe Quarkus app uses SmallRye Reactive Messaging with in-memory channels (no external broker). In Spring Boot, we'll replace this with a simple in-memory event system using Spring's `ApplicationEventPublisher` and `@EventListener`.\n\n### Files to rewrite:\n\n**1. MessageProducerService.java** (messaging/)\nOriginal uses:\n- `@ApplicationScoped`\n- `@Inject @Channel(\"trade-broker-queue\") @Broadcast Emitter<OrderMessage> brokerEmitter`\n- `@Inject @Channel(\"trade-streamer-topic\") @Broadcast Emitter<QuoteUpdateMessage> streamerEmitter`\n\nRewrite to use Spring:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\n\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n\n@Service\npublic class MessageProducerService {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private ApplicationEventPublisher eventPublisher;\n\n    public void queueOrderForProcessing(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.newOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:queueOrderForProcessing - sending order \" + orderID);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new BrokerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n\n    public void sendBrokerPing(String text) {\n        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.ping(text);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendBrokerPing - sending ping\");\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new BrokerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n\n    public void publishQuoteUpdate(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, newPrice, oldPrice);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuoteUpdate - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new StreamerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n\n    public void publishQuotePriceChange(String symbol, String company, BigDecimal price,\n            BigDecimal oldPrice, BigDecimal open, BigDecimal low, BigDecimal high,\n            double volume, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) {\n        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, price, oldPrice);\n        message.setCompany(company);\n        message.setOpen(open);\n        message.setLow(low);\n        message.setHigh(high);\n        message.setVolume(volume);\n        message.setChangeFactor(changeFactor);\n        message.setSharesTraded(sharesTraded);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuotePriceChange - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new StreamerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n\n    public void sendStreamerPing(String text) {\n        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.ping(text);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendStreamerPing - sending ping\");\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new StreamerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**2. Create BrokerMessageEvent.java** (messaging/) - NEW FILE:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationEvent;\n\npublic class BrokerMessageEvent extends ApplicationEvent {\n    private final OrderMessage message;\n\n    public BrokerMessageEvent(Object source, OrderMessage message) {\n        super(source);\n        this.message = message;\n    }\n\n    public OrderMessage getMessage() {\n        return message;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**3. Create StreamerMessageEvent.java** (messaging/) - NEW FILE:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationEvent;\n\npublic class StreamerMessageEvent extends ApplicationEvent {\n    private final QuoteUpdateMessage message;\n\n    public StreamerMessageEvent(Object source, QuoteUpdateMessage message) {\n        super(source);\n        this.message = message;\n    }\n\n    public QuoteUpdateMessage getMessage() {\n        return message;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**4. DTBroker3MDB.java** (mdb/)\nOriginal uses:\n- `@ApplicationScoped`\n- `@Incoming(\"trade-broker-queue\")`\n- `@Transactional`\n\nRewrite to use Spring `@EventListener`:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n\nimport jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.BrokerMessageEvent;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.OrderMessage;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n\n@Component\npublic class DTBroker3MDB {\n  \n  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n  private int statInterval = 10000;\n\n  @Autowired\n  TradeServices trade;\n\n  public DTBroker3MDB() {\n    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n      statInterval = 10000;\n    }\n    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n  }   \n\n  @PostConstruct\n  void init() {\n    Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:init()\");\n  } \n  \n  @EventListener\n  @Transactional\n  public void onMessage(BrokerMessageEvent event) {\n    OrderMessage message = event.getMessage();\n    try {\n      Log.trace(\"TradeBroker:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"command-->\"\n          + message.getCommand() + \"<--\");\n\n      String command = message.getCommand();\n      if (command == null) {\n        Log.debug(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n        return;\n      }\n      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"neworder\")) {\n        Integer orderID = message.getOrderID();\n        boolean twoPhase = message.isTwoPhase();\n        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n\n        try {\n          Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - completing order \" + orderID + \" twoPhase=\" + twoPhase);\n          trade.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n\n          TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:neworder\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n\n          if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n            Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: processed \" + statInterval + \" stock trading orders.\" +\n                \" Total NewOrders process = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n                \"Time (in seconds):\" +\n                \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n                \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n                \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n          }\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n          Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage Exception completing order: \" + orderID + \"\\n\", e);\n          throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to complete order: \" + orderID, e);\n        }\n      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n        Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage  received test command -- message: \" + message.getText());\n\n        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n\n        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n\n        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n          Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n              \" Total ping message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n        }\n      } else {\n        Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + message.getText());\n      }\n    } catch (Throwable t) {\n      Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB: Exception\", t);\n      throw new RuntimeException(\"DTBroker3MDB processing failed\", t);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**5. DTStreamer3MDB.java** (mdb/)\nRewrite similarly - use `@EventListener` for `StreamerMessageEvent`:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.StreamerMessageEvent;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.QuoteUpdateMessage;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n\n@Component\npublic class DTStreamer3MDB {\n\n  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n  private int statInterval = 10000;\n\n  public DTStreamer3MDB() {\n    Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:DTStreamer3MDB()\");\n    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n      statInterval = 10000;\n    }\n    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n  }\n\n  @EventListener\n  public void onMessage(StreamerMessageEvent event) {\n    QuoteUpdateMessage message = event.getMessage();\n    try {\n      Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"command-->\"\n          + message.getCommand() + \"<--\");\n      \n      String command = message.getCommand();\n      if (command == null) {\n        Log.debug(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n        return;\n      }\n      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"updateQuote\")) {\n        Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"\\n\\t symbol = \"\n              + message.getSymbol() + \"\\n\\t current price =\" + message.getPrice() + \"\\n\\t old price =\"\n              + message.getOldPrice());\n        \n        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n\n        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTStreamer3MDB:updateQuote\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n\n        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n          Log.log(\" DTStreamer3MDB: \" + statInterval + \" prices updated:\" +\n              \" Total message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs() );\n        }\n      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n        Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage  received ping command -- message: \" + message.getText());\n\n        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n\n        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTStreamer3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n\n        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n          Log.log(\" DTStreamer3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n              \" Total message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n        }\n      } else {\n        Log.error(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + message.getText());\n      }\n    } catch (Throwable t) {\n      Log.error(\"DTStreamer3MDB: Exception\", t);\n      throw new RuntimeException(\"DTStreamer3MDB processing failed\", t);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**6. QuoteUpdateMessage.java and OrderMessage.java** (messaging/) - These are POJOs. Read them and check if they have any Quarkus imports. If not, leave them as-is.\n\nRead each file first, then write the new version. Create the 2 new event files. Report what was done.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":602,"cache_read_input_tokens":130573,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":602,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":10017},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"8cc54638-f357-45a9-aeb5-f56638ed1f94"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01BUPSw2daEAzTLjakJtxx5Z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_013YQ23j7xdDjmd1NyqdxWeV","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Rewrite startup/util/interface classes","prompt":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need to rewrite startup, utility, and interface classes.\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\n### File 1: DatabasePopulator.java (startup/)\nRead and rewrite. Original uses:\n- `@ApplicationScoped` \n- `@Observes StartupEvent` (Quarkus)\n- `@ConfigProperty` (MicroProfile)\n- `@Inject EntityManager`\n- `@Transactional`\n\nRewrite to:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\n\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;\nimport org.springframework.boot.context.event.ApplicationReadyEvent;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n\n@Component\npublic class DatabasePopulator {\n\n    @PersistenceContext\n    EntityManager em;\n\n    @Value(\"${trade.db.populate.on.startup:true}\")\n    boolean populateOnStartup;\n\n    @Value(\"${trade.max-users:50}\")\n    int maxUsers;\n\n    @Value(\"${trade.max-quotes:100}\")\n    int maxQuotes;\n\n    @EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent.class)\n    @Transactional\n    public void onStart() {\n        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        try {\n            Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n            if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n                return;\n            }\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            // Table may not exist yet, proceed with population\n            Log.log(\"Database tables being created, will populate...\");\n        }\n\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n        \n        try {\n            populateQuotes();\n            populateUsers();\n            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating database\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void populateQuotes() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n        \n        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n            \n            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n            quote.setPrice(price);\n            quote.setOpen(price);\n            quote.setLow(price);\n            quote.setHigh(price);\n            quote.setChange(0.0);\n            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n            \n            em.persist(quote);\n            \n            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n            }\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n\n    private void populateUsers() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n        \n        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n            \n            if (i == 0) {\n                initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000);\n            }\n            \n            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n            profile.setUserID(userID);\n            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n            profile.setAddress(address);\n            profile.setEmail(email);\n            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n            em.persist(profile);\n            \n            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n            account.setProfile(profile);\n            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setLoginCount(0);\n            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n            em.persist(account);\n            \n            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID + \" with balance: \" + initialBalance);\n            }\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### File 2: RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java (util/)\nRead and rewrite. Replace CDI `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Component`. Replace CDI `Event` with Spring's `ApplicationEventPublisher`.\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n\n@Component\npublic class RecentQuotePriceChangeList {\n\n    private List<QuoteDataBean> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    private int maxSize = 5;\n\n    public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n        int symbolNumber = Integer.parseInt(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n\n        if (symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n            list.add(0, quoteData);\n            if (list.size() > maxSize) {\n                list.remove(maxSize);\n            }\n        }\n        return true;\n    }\n\n    public boolean isEmpty() {\n        return list.isEmpty();\n    }\n\n    public List<QuoteDataBean> recentList() {\n        return list;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### File 3-8: Interface files (interfaces/)\nRead all interface files and check if they need changes:\n- `TradeServices.java` - Pure interface, no framework imports needed. Leave as-is.\n- `TradeDB.java` - Pure interface. Leave as-is.\n- `RuntimeMode.java` - CDI qualifier annotation. We don't need this in Spring. We can either delete it or make it a no-op. SIMPLEST: Keep the file but make it a simple annotation (no CDI qualifier):\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface RuntimeMode {\n    String value() default \"\";\n}\n```\n\n- `QuotePriceChange.java` - CDI qualifier. Same treatment:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface QuotePriceChange {\n}\n```\n\n- `MarketSummaryUpdate.java` - CDI qualifier. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface MarketSummaryUpdate {\n}\n```\n\n- `TradeSession2Direct.java` - CDI qualifier. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface TradeSession2Direct {\n}\n```\n\n- `TradeJDBC.java` - CDI qualifier. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface TradeJDBC {\n}\n```\n\n- `TradeEJB.java` - CDI qualifier. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface TradeEJB {\n}\n```\n\n- `Trace.java` - CDI interceptor binding. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD})\npublic @interface Trace {\n}\n```\n\n### File 9: TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java (util/)\nThis is a CDI `AnnotationLiteral`. Read it and simplify - it won't be used in Spring but keep it compilable:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Annotation;\n\npublic class TradeRunTimeModeLiteral implements RuntimeMode {\n    private final String value;\n\n    public TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(String value) {\n        this.value = value;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public String value() {\n        return value;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Class<? extends Annotation> annotationType() {\n        return RuntimeMode.class;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Other util files to check:\n- `TradeConfig.java` - Read it. It's a plain Java class with no framework imports. Leave as-is.\n- `TimerStat.java` - Plain POJO. Leave as-is.\n- `KeyBlock.java` - Plain Java. Leave as-is.\n- `Log.java` - Plain Java. Leave as-is.\n- `FinancialUtils.java` - Plain Java. Leave as-is.\n- `MDBStats.java` - Plain Java singleton. Leave as-is.\n- `KeySequenceDirect.java` (impl/direct/) - Plain Java. Leave as-is.\n\nRead each file, write the updated version. Report back what was changed.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":602,"cache_read_input_tokens":130573,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":602,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":10017},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"253cee9f-e13d-44c2-b9c0-e05565a8678a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need to rewrite 4 REST resource files from JAX-RS (Quarkus) to Spring MVC (Spring Boot).\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\nIMPORTANT: The application.properties sets `spring.mvc.servlet.path=/rest` which means all Spring MVC endpoints are automatically prefixed with `/rest`. So paths in the controllers should NOT include `/rest`.\n\nIMPORTANT: In the original Quarkus app, `TradeServices` was injected via CDI `@Inject`. In Spring, this becomes `@Autowired` or constructor injection. Since `TradeServices` is an interface with multiple implementations, we need to use `@Qualifier` or `@Primary`. The `TradeSLSBBean` is the default (was `@Default` in CDI).\n\n### File 1: TradeResource.java\nRead `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/TradeResource.java` and rewrite it:\n\nReplace:\n- `jakarta.ws.rs.*` imports → `org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped` → `@RestController`\n- `jakarta.inject.Inject` → `@Autowired`\n- `@Path(\"trade\")` → `@RequestMapping(\"/trade\")`\n- `@GET @Path(\"/market\")` → `@GetMapping(\"/market\")`\n- `@POST @Path(\"/login\")` → `@PostMapping(\"/login\")`\n- `@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)` → nothing (use @RequestParam)\n- `@FormParam(\"x\")` → `@RequestParam(\"x\")`\n- `@PathParam(\"x\")` → `@PathVariable(\"x\")`\n- `@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)` → (handled by @RestController)\n- `Response.ok(x).build()` → `ResponseEntity.ok(x)`\n- `Response.serverError().entity(x).build()` → `ResponseEntity.status(500).body(x)`\n- `Response.status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED)` → `ResponseEntity.status(401)`\n- `Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build()` → `ResponseEntity.notFound().build()`\n- `Response` return type → `ResponseEntity<?>`\n\n### File 2: QuoteResource.java\nRead and rewrite similarly:\n- Same JAX-RS → Spring MVC conversion\n- `@Path(\"quotes\")` → `@RequestMapping(\"/quotes\")`\n\n### File 3: MessagingResource.java\nRead and rewrite similarly:\n- `@Path(\"/messaging\")` → `@RequestMapping(\"/messaging\")`\n- `@QueryParam` → `@RequestParam`\n\n### File 4: TradeAppResource.java (at web/TradeAppResource.java)\nRead and rewrite similarly:\n- `@Path(\"/app\")` → `@RequestMapping(\"/app\")`\n- `@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)` → methods return `ResponseEntity<String>` with `produces = \"text/html\"`\n- Update form action URLs from `/rest/app` to `/rest/app` (keep as-is since spring.mvc.servlet.path=/rest handles it)\n\nFor ALL files, use `@Autowired` for TradeServices injection. Since we'll mark TradeSLSBBean as `@Primary`, no qualifier is needed.\n\nRead each file first, then write the updated version."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012M7gsRgZQL4Pbtw8LRDtTj","session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"3f1d1bbc-53d8-4032-93e2-6d88f352cdee"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need to rewrite all service implementation classes.\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\nMigration rules:\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` → `@org.springframework.stereotype.Service`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped` → `@org.springframework.stereotype.Service` with `@org.springframework.context.annotation.Scope(\"prototype\")`  \n- `jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent` → `@org.springframework.stereotype.Component` with `@org.springframework.context.annotation.Scope(\"prototype\")`\n- `jakarta.inject.Inject` → `@org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired`\n- `jakarta.transaction.Transactional` → `@org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional`\n- `jakarta.persistence.EntityManager` with `@Inject` → `@PersistenceContext EntityManager`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.event.Event` → Remove (replace with Spring's ApplicationEventPublisher or simply remove unused events)\n- `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Default` → Remove\n- `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any` / `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance` → Remove/simplify\n- CDI qualifier annotations like `@TradeEJB`, `@TradeJDBC`, `@TradeSession2Direct` → Use Spring `@Qualifier`\n- `@RuntimeMode(\"...\")` → Remove (custom CDI qualifier)\n- `@Trace` → Remove (custom CDI interceptor binding)\n- `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled` → `@org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Scheduled`\n- `io.quarkus.virtual.threads.VirtualThreads` → Use standard Java `Executors.newVirtualThreadPerTaskExecutor()` or `Executors.newCachedThreadPool()`\n- `io.quarkus.narayana.jta.QuarkusTransaction` → Remove (not used directly)\n- `io.agroal.api.AgroalDataSource` → `javax.sql.DataSource`\n- `org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty` → `@org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value`\n- `io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent` → Use `@PostConstruct` or `ApplicationReadyEvent`\n- `jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes` → Remove (use Spring event or @PostConstruct)\n- `@jakarta.annotation.Resource` → `@Autowired`\n- `jakarta.transaction.UserTransaction` → Remove (use Spring's `@Transactional` or `PlatformTransactionManager`)\n- CDI `Event<String>` for firing async events → Remove or replace with `ApplicationEventPublisher`\n- `@io.smallrye.reactive.messaging.annotations.Broadcast` → Remove\n- `org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel` → Remove  \n- `org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter` → Remove\n- `org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming` → Remove\n- `@jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull` / `@NotEmpty` → Keep (works with Spring validation)\n- `jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct` → Keep (works in Spring)\n\n### Files to rewrite:\n\n**1. TradeSLSBBean.java** (impl/ejb3/) - This is the PRIMARY TradeServices implementation. Mark it with `@Service` and `@Primary`. Replace `@Inject EntityManager` with `@PersistenceContext EntityManager`. Replace `@Inject MessageProducerService` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject MarketSummarySingleton` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject RecentQuotePriceChangeList` with `@Autowired`. Remove `@Default`, `@TradeEJB`, `@RuntimeMode`, `@Trace`. Keep `@Transactional` but change to Spring's. Keep all business logic exactly the same.\n\n**2. MarketSummarySingleton.java** (impl/ejb3/) - Replace `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Service`. Replace `@Inject EntityManager` with `@PersistenceContext`. Replace `@Inject @MarketSummaryUpdate Event<String>` with removal (or `@Autowired ApplicationEventPublisher`). Replace `@Scheduled(every = \"20s\")` with `@Scheduled(fixedRate = 20000)`. The method `updateMarketSummary()` needs `@Transactional` since it accesses the EntityManager.\n\n**3. AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java** (impl/ejb3/) - Replace `@RequestScoped` with `@Component @Scope(\"prototype\")`. Remove `@Inject @VirtualThreads ExecutorService` - instead create a regular ExecutorService field. Replace `@Inject AsyncScheduledOrder` with `@Autowired ApplicationContext` and get bean from context (since it's prototype-scoped).\n\n**4. AsyncScheduledOrder.java** (impl/ejb3/) - Replace `@Dependent` with `@Component @Scope(\"prototype\")`. The constructor currently uses CDI `Instance<TradeServices>` with qualifiers. In Spring, just inject the primary `TradeServices` with `@Autowired`.\n\n**5. TradeDirect.java** (impl/direct/) - Replace `@Dependent` with `@Component(\"tradeDirect\") @Scope(\"prototype\")`. Replace `@Inject DataSource` with `@Autowired DataSource`. Replace `@Inject UserTransaction` → Remove UserTransaction, manage transactions manually via DataSource connections (already does manual commits). Replace `@Inject RecentQuotePriceChangeList` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject AsyncOrderSubmitter` with `@Autowired`. Replace `@Inject @MarketSummaryUpdate Event<String>` with nothing (remove). Replace `@Inject MessageProducerService` with `@Autowired`. Remove `@TradeJDBC`, `@RuntimeMode`, `@Trace` qualifiers. Remove `io.quarkus.narayana.jta.QuarkusTransaction` import.\n\n**6. TradeDirectDBUtils.java** (impl/direct/) - Replace `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Service`. Replace `@Inject AgroalDataSource` with `@Autowired DataSource`. Replace `@Inject @TradeJDBC TradeServices` with `@Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\") TradeServices`.\n\n**7. AsyncOrder.java** (impl/direct/) - Replace `@Dependent` with `@Component @Scope(\"prototype\")`. Replace `@Inject @TradeJDBC TradeServices` with `@Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\") TradeServices`. Keep `@Transactional` but use Spring's.\n\n**8. AsyncOrderSubmitter.java** (impl/direct/) - Replace `@RequestScoped` with `@Component @Scope(\"prototype\")`. Remove `@VirtualThreads`. Use `Executors.newCachedThreadPool()`.\n\n**9. DirectSLSBBean.java** (impl/session2direct/) - Replace `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Service(\"directSLSBBean\")`. Replace `@Inject @TradeJDBC TradeServices` with `@Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\") TradeServices`. Replace `@Inject AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter` with `@Autowired`. Remove `@TradeSession2Direct`, `@RuntimeMode`, `@Trace`. Keep `@Transactional` but Spring's.\n\nRead each file, rewrite it with the above transformations. Preserve ALL business logic exactly. Just change annotations and imports.\n\nCRITICAL: For TradeDirect.java, the `UserTransaction txn` field that was injected is used for global transactions. Since Spring doesn't have UserTransaction in the same way, replace the `txn` field with `@Autowired PlatformTransactionManager transactionManager` and use `TransactionStatus` / `TransactionTemplate` OR simply remove the UserTransaction usage since the direct JDBC mode already manages its own commits/rollbacks via Connection. The easiest approach: replace `txn.begin()`, `txn.commit()`, `txn.rollback()` with NO-OP or with connection-level transaction management that's already in place. Actually, the safest is to just use `@Autowired org.springframework.transaction.PlatformTransactionManager txnManager` and then `TransactionDefinition def = new DefaultTransactionDefinition(); TransactionStatus status = txnManager.getTransaction(def);` etc. But that's complex. The simplest: just keep the field but autowire a `javax.transaction.UserTransaction` - but Spring doesn't provide one directly.\n\nSIMPLEST APPROACH for TradeDirect: Remove UserTransaction entirely. The code already has manual connection commit/rollback. For the `ASYNCH_2PHASE` mode paths that use `txn.begin()/commit()/rollback()`, simply make the transaction boundary be managed by the connection itself (the connection is already not auto-commit). Set `inGlobalTxn=false` always in those paths so the existing connection-level commit/rollback handles it."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Uc6kGPVjfMPcWC9DhiMNbo","session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"f2b6329e-b8ef-46e2-bb66-ba1dcbb97efe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need to rewrite the messaging classes.\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\nThe Quarkus app uses SmallRye Reactive Messaging with in-memory channels (no external broker). In Spring Boot, we'll replace this with a simple in-memory event system using Spring's `ApplicationEventPublisher` and `@EventListener`.\n\n### Files to rewrite:\n\n**1. MessageProducerService.java** (messaging/)\nOriginal uses:\n- `@ApplicationScoped`\n- `@Inject @Channel(\"trade-broker-queue\") @Broadcast Emitter<OrderMessage> brokerEmitter`\n- `@Inject @Channel(\"trade-streamer-topic\") @Broadcast Emitter<QuoteUpdateMessage> streamerEmitter`\n\nRewrite to use Spring:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\n\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n\n@Service\npublic class MessageProducerService {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private ApplicationEventPublisher eventPublisher;\n\n    public void queueOrderForProcessing(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.newOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:queueOrderForProcessing - sending order \" + orderID);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new BrokerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n\n    public void sendBrokerPing(String text) {\n        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.ping(text);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendBrokerPing - sending ping\");\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new BrokerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n\n    public void publishQuoteUpdate(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, newPrice, oldPrice);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuoteUpdate - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new StreamerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n\n    public void publishQuotePriceChange(String symbol, String company, BigDecimal price,\n            BigDecimal oldPrice, BigDecimal open, BigDecimal low, BigDecimal high,\n            double volume, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) {\n        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, price, oldPrice);\n        message.setCompany(company);\n        message.setOpen(open);\n        message.setLow(low);\n        message.setHigh(high);\n        message.setVolume(volume);\n        message.setChangeFactor(changeFactor);\n        message.setSharesTraded(sharesTraded);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuotePriceChange - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new StreamerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n\n    public void sendStreamerPing(String text) {\n        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.ping(text);\n        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendStreamerPing - sending ping\");\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new StreamerMessageEvent(this, message));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**2. Create BrokerMessageEvent.java** (messaging/) - NEW FILE:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationEvent;\n\npublic class BrokerMessageEvent extends ApplicationEvent {\n    private final OrderMessage message;\n\n    public BrokerMessageEvent(Object source, OrderMessage message) {\n        super(source);\n        this.message = message;\n    }\n\n    public OrderMessage getMessage() {\n        return message;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**3. Create StreamerMessageEvent.java** (messaging/) - NEW FILE:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationEvent;\n\npublic class StreamerMessageEvent extends ApplicationEvent {\n    private final QuoteUpdateMessage message;\n\n    public StreamerMessageEvent(Object source, QuoteUpdateMessage message) {\n        super(source);\n        this.message = message;\n    }\n\n    public QuoteUpdateMessage getMessage() {\n        return message;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**4. DTBroker3MDB.java** (mdb/)\nOriginal uses:\n- `@ApplicationScoped`\n- `@Incoming(\"trade-broker-queue\")`\n- `@Transactional`\n\nRewrite to use Spring `@EventListener`:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n\nimport jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.BrokerMessageEvent;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.OrderMessage;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n\n@Component\npublic class DTBroker3MDB {\n  \n  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n  private int statInterval = 10000;\n\n  @Autowired\n  TradeServices trade;\n\n  public DTBroker3MDB() {\n    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n      statInterval = 10000;\n    }\n    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n  }   \n\n  @PostConstruct\n  void init() {\n    Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:init()\");\n  } \n  \n  @EventListener\n  @Transactional\n  public void onMessage(BrokerMessageEvent event) {\n    OrderMessage message = event.getMessage();\n    try {\n      Log.trace(\"TradeBroker:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"command-->\"\n          + message.getCommand() + \"<--\");\n\n      String command = message.getCommand();\n      if (command == null) {\n        Log.debug(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n        return;\n      }\n      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"neworder\")) {\n        Integer orderID = message.getOrderID();\n        boolean twoPhase = message.isTwoPhase();\n        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n\n        try {\n          Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - completing order \" + orderID + \" twoPhase=\" + twoPhase);\n          trade.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n\n          TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:neworder\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n\n          if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n            Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: processed \" + statInterval + \" stock trading orders.\" +\n                \" Total NewOrders process = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n                \"Time (in seconds):\" +\n                \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n                \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n                \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n          }\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n          Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage Exception completing order: \" + orderID + \"\\n\", e);\n          throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to complete order: \" + orderID, e);\n        }\n      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n        Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage  received test command -- message: \" + message.getText());\n\n        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n\n        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n\n        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n          Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n              \" Total ping message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n        }\n      } else {\n        Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + message.getText());\n      }\n    } catch (Throwable t) {\n      Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB: Exception\", t);\n      throw new RuntimeException(\"DTBroker3MDB processing failed\", t);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**5. DTStreamer3MDB.java** (mdb/)\nRewrite similarly - use `@EventListener` for `StreamerMessageEvent`:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.StreamerMessageEvent;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.QuoteUpdateMessage;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n\n@Component\npublic class DTStreamer3MDB {\n\n  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n  private int statInterval = 10000;\n\n  public DTStreamer3MDB() {\n    Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:DTStreamer3MDB()\");\n    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n      statInterval = 10000;\n    }\n    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n  }\n\n  @EventListener\n  public void onMessage(StreamerMessageEvent event) {\n    QuoteUpdateMessage message = event.getMessage();\n    try {\n      Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"command-->\"\n          + message.getCommand() + \"<--\");\n      \n      String command = message.getCommand();\n      if (command == null) {\n        Log.debug(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n        return;\n      }\n      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"updateQuote\")) {\n        Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"\\n\\t symbol = \"\n              + message.getSymbol() + \"\\n\\t current price =\" + message.getPrice() + \"\\n\\t old price =\"\n              + message.getOldPrice());\n        \n        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n\n        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTStreamer3MDB:updateQuote\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n\n        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n          Log.log(\" DTStreamer3MDB: \" + statInterval + \" prices updated:\" +\n              \" Total message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs() );\n        }\n      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n        Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage  received ping command -- message: \" + message.getText());\n\n        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n\n        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTStreamer3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n\n        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n          Log.log(\" DTStreamer3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n              \" Total message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n        }\n      } else {\n        Log.error(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + message.getText());\n      }\n    } catch (Throwable t) {\n      Log.error(\"DTStreamer3MDB: Exception\", t);\n      throw new RuntimeException(\"DTStreamer3MDB processing failed\", t);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**6. QuoteUpdateMessage.java and OrderMessage.java** (messaging/) - These are POJOs. Read them and check if they have any Quarkus imports. If not, leave them as-is.\n\nRead each file first, then write the new version. Create the 2 new event files. Report what was done."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UsBY2Qg5wdBJM2V5RHeTYS","session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"b04962d3-3b6c-4aed-8be2-cdf878096849"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Quarkus app to Spring Boot. I need to rewrite startup, utility, and interface classes.\n\nWorking directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output\n\n### File 1: DatabasePopulator.java (startup/)\nRead and rewrite. Original uses:\n- `@ApplicationScoped` \n- `@Observes StartupEvent` (Quarkus)\n- `@ConfigProperty` (MicroProfile)\n- `@Inject EntityManager`\n- `@Transactional`\n\nRewrite to:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\n\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;\nimport org.springframework.boot.context.event.ApplicationReadyEvent;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n\n@Component\npublic class DatabasePopulator {\n\n    @PersistenceContext\n    EntityManager em;\n\n    @Value(\"${trade.db.populate.on.startup:true}\")\n    boolean populateOnStartup;\n\n    @Value(\"${trade.max-users:50}\")\n    int maxUsers;\n\n    @Value(\"${trade.max-quotes:100}\")\n    int maxQuotes;\n\n    @EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent.class)\n    @Transactional\n    public void onStart() {\n        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        try {\n            Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n            if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n                return;\n            }\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            // Table may not exist yet, proceed with population\n            Log.log(\"Database tables being created, will populate...\");\n        }\n\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n        \n        try {\n            populateQuotes();\n            populateUsers();\n            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating database\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void populateQuotes() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n        \n        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n            \n            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n            quote.setPrice(price);\n            quote.setOpen(price);\n            quote.setLow(price);\n            quote.setHigh(price);\n            quote.setChange(0.0);\n            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n            \n            em.persist(quote);\n            \n            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n            }\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n\n    private void populateUsers() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n        \n        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n            \n            if (i == 0) {\n                initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000);\n            }\n            \n            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n            profile.setUserID(userID);\n            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n            profile.setAddress(address);\n            profile.setEmail(email);\n            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n            em.persist(profile);\n            \n            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n            account.setProfile(profile);\n            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setLoginCount(0);\n            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n            em.persist(account);\n            \n            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID + \" with balance: \" + initialBalance);\n            }\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### File 2: RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java (util/)\nRead and rewrite. Replace CDI `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Component`. Replace CDI `Event` with Spring's `ApplicationEventPublisher`.\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n\n@Component\npublic class RecentQuotePriceChangeList {\n\n    private List<QuoteDataBean> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    private int maxSize = 5;\n\n    public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n        int symbolNumber = Integer.parseInt(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n\n        if (symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n            list.add(0, quoteData);\n            if (list.size() > maxSize) {\n                list.remove(maxSize);\n            }\n        }\n        return true;\n    }\n\n    public boolean isEmpty() {\n        return list.isEmpty();\n    }\n\n    public List<QuoteDataBean> recentList() {\n        return list;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### File 3-8: Interface files (interfaces/)\nRead all interface files and check if they need changes:\n- `TradeServices.java` - Pure interface, no framework imports needed. Leave as-is.\n- `TradeDB.java` - Pure interface. Leave as-is.\n- `RuntimeMode.java` - CDI qualifier annotation. We don't need this in Spring. We can either delete it or make it a no-op. SIMPLEST: Keep the file but make it a simple annotation (no CDI qualifier):\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface RuntimeMode {\n    String value() default \"\";\n}\n```\n\n- `QuotePriceChange.java` - CDI qualifier. Same treatment:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface QuotePriceChange {\n}\n```\n\n- `MarketSummaryUpdate.java` - CDI qualifier. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface MarketSummaryUpdate {\n}\n```\n\n- `TradeSession2Direct.java` - CDI qualifier. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface TradeSession2Direct {\n}\n```\n\n- `TradeJDBC.java` - CDI qualifier. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface TradeJDBC {\n}\n```\n\n- `TradeEJB.java` - CDI qualifier. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD})\npublic @interface TradeEJB {\n}\n```\n\n- `Trace.java` - CDI interceptor binding. Same:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD})\npublic @interface Trace {\n}\n```\n\n### File 9: TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java (util/)\nThis is a CDI `AnnotationLiteral`. Read it and simplify - it won't be used in Spring but keep it compilable:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Annotation;\n\npublic class TradeRunTimeModeLiteral implements RuntimeMode {\n    private final String value;\n\n    public TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(String value) {\n        this.value = value;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public String value() {\n        return value;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Class<? extends Annotation> annotationType() {\n        return RuntimeMode.class;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Other util files to check:\n- `TradeConfig.java` - Read it. It's a plain Java class with no framework imports. Leave as-is.\n- `TimerStat.java` - Plain POJO. Leave as-is.\n- `KeyBlock.java` - Plain Java. Leave as-is.\n- `Log.java` - Plain Java. Leave as-is.\n- `FinancialUtils.java` - Plain Java. Leave as-is.\n- `MDBStats.java` - Plain Java singleton. Leave as-is.\n- `KeySequenceDirect.java` (impl/direct/) - Plain Java. Leave as-is.\n\nRead each file, write the updated version. Report back what was changed."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013YQ23j7xdDjmd1NyqdxWeV","session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"8a3e92da-8265-4541-a4bb-2e5b1ab8b1c6"}
