{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012M7gsRgZQL4Pbtw8LRDtTj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully migrated all 4 REST resource files from JAX-RS (Quarkus) to Spring MVC (Spring Boot). Here's a detailed summary of what was done:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\n### File 1: TradeResource.java\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/TradeResource.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Replaced `jakarta.ws.rs.*` imports with Spring MVC annotations (`org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*`)\n- Changed `@RequestScoped` to `@RestController`\n- Changed `@Inject` to `@Autowired`\n- Changed `@Path(\"trade\")` to `@RequestMapping(\"/trade\")`\n- Converted all JAX-RS method annotations to Spring equivalents:\n  - `@GET` → `@GetMapping`\n  - `@POST` → `@PostMapping`\n  - `@Path(\"/market\")` → `@GetMapping(\"/market\")`\n  - `@PathParam` → `@PathVariable`\n  - `@FormParam` → `@RequestParam`\n- Changed return type from `Response` to `ResponseEntity<?>`\n- Converted response builders:\n  - `Response.ok(x).build()` → `ResponseEntity.ok(x)`\n  - `Response.serverError().entity(x).build()` → `ResponseEntity.status(500).body(x)`\n  - `Response.status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED)` → `ResponseEntity.status(401)`\n  - `Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build()` → `ResponseEntity.notFound().build()`\n- Removed `@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)` and `@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)` (handled automatically by `@RestController`)\n\n### File 2: QuoteResource.java\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/QuoteResource.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Migrated from JAX-RS to Spring MVC with same pattern as TradeResource\n- Changed `@Path(\"quotes\")` to `@RequestMapping(\"/quotes\")`\n- Changed `@GET @Path(\"/{symbols}\")` to `@GetMapping(\"/{symbols}\")`\n- Changed `@POST` (with no path) to `@PostMapping` \n- Replaced `@PathParam` with `@PathVariable`\n- Replaced `@FormParam` with `@RequestParam`\n- Return type changed from `List<QuoteDataBean>` directly (Spring handles JSON serialization automatically)\n\n### File 3: MessagingResource.java\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/MessagingResource.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Same JAX-RS to Spring MVC migration pattern\n- Changed `@Path(\"/messaging\")` to `@RequestMapping(\"/messaging\")`\n- Replaced `@QueryParam` with `@RequestParam` (added `required = false` for optional parameters)\n- All Response objects converted to ResponseEntity\n- Updated comments to reference \"Spring Boot endpoints\" instead of \"Quarkus endpoints\"\n\n### File 4: TradeAppResource.java\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/TradeAppResource.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Changed `@Path(\"/app\")` to `@RequestMapping(\"/app\")`\n- Changed `@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)` to `produces = MediaType.TEXT_HTML_VALUE` on method level\n- All `@GET` methods now return `ResponseEntity<String>` with `produces = MediaType.TEXT_HTML_VALUE`\n- All `@POST` methods now return `ResponseEntity<String>` with `produces = MediaType.TEXT_HTML_VALUE`\n- Replaced `@QueryParam` with `@RequestParam` (all marked as `required = false`)\n- Replaced `@FormParam` with `@RequestParam` (all marked as `required = false`)\n- All `Response.ok(html).build()` converted to `ResponseEntity.ok(html)`\n- Updated footer text from \"Quarkus Edition\" to \"Spring Boot Edition\"\n- Form action URLs kept as `/rest/app` (correct because `spring.mvc.servlet.path=/rest` handles the prefix automatically)\n\n## Important Notes:\n\n1. **Path Prefix**: All controller paths DO NOT include `/rest` because the `application.properties` setting `spring.mvc.servlet.path=/rest` automatically prefixes all Spring MVC endpoints.\n\n2. **Dependency Injection**: Using `@Autowired` for `TradeServices` injection. Since `TradeSLSBBean` will be marked as `@Primary`, no `@Qualifier` is needed.\n\n3. **JSON Serialization**: Spring's `@RestController` handles JSON serialization automatically, so explicit `@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)` annotations are not needed.\n\n4. **Form Parameters**: All form parameters are now handled via `@RequestParam` instead of `@FormParam`, and optional parameters are marked with `required = false`.\n\n5. **Response Handling**: All JAX-RS `Response` objects have been converted to Spring's `ResponseEntity<?>` with appropriate HTTP status codes.\n\nAll files have been successfully migrated and are ready for use with Spring Boot!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f3099ad-61fc-4987-ab0b-e3abd721a458","uuid":"e5e56571-b5b3-44eb-8682-20c239e0536a"}
